.TH MCP-KODI 1 "June 2026" "mcp-kodi 0.2.0dev" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mcp-kodi \- MCP server for controlling Kodi over JSON-RPC
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mcp-kodi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mcp-kodi
is a Model Context Protocol (MCP) server that lets an AI assistant control a
Kodi media player through Kodi's JSON-RPC API. It is written in C on the GLib
stack.
.PP
There is no user-facing command line: the assistant calls the server's tools,
and the server speaks JSON-RPC to Kodi. The only interface is MCP over standard
input and output \(em the program reads JSON-RPC messages from stdin and writes
responses to stdout until stdin reaches end-of-file. Diagnostic messages are
written to standard error.
.PP
.B mcp-kodi
takes no command-line options or arguments. It is normally launched by an MCP
client rather than run interactively.
.SH CONFIGURATION
At startup the server reads its configuration once from
.IR ${XDG_CONFIG_HOME:-~/.config}/mcp-kodi/config.json .
The file holds a map of named Kodi instances and names one as the
.IR default ,
used whenever a tool call omits an explicit instance.
.PP
Each instance entry may set
.IR host ,
.I auth
(HTTP Basic credentials as
.IR user:pass ,
never returned by the tools),
.I scheme
.RI ( http
or
.IR https ),
.IR insecure ,
and
.I allow_rpc
(opt-in gate for the raw JSON-RPC escape hatch, set only by hand-editing the
file).
.PP
With no configuration file present, a single instance can be defined from the
environment (see
.B ENVIRONMENT
below). With neither a file nor environment variables, the server exits with an
error describing how to configure it.
.PP
Configuration is read only at startup; after editing
.IR config.json ,
restart the server so it re-reads the file.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B KODI_HOST
Host (and optional port) of an implicit
.I default
instance.
.TP
.B KODI_AUTH
HTTP Basic credentials as
.IR user:pass .
.TP
.B KODI_SCHEME
.I http
or
.IR https .
.TP
.B KODI_CURL_OPTS
A
.B \-k
here maps to the instance's
.I insecure
flag.
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Base directory for the configuration file; defaults to
.IR ~/.config .
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ${XDG_CONFIG_HOME:-~/.config}/mcp-kodi/config.json
Per-user configuration. Stores Kodi passwords in plaintext with mode 0600;
protect it accordingly.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 on a clean shutdown (stdin EOF). Returns non-zero if configuration
cannot be loaded.
.SH SEE ALSO
Project documentation and the MCP specification at
.UR https://modelcontextprotocol.io
.UE .
